      • INITIAL_STATE

        static final String INITIAL_STATE
        Deprecated. will be removed after 3.5
        Constant representing a version in the repository without any content.
        Such version branches has to be created while initializing the repository on the very first time.

        ID: "init"

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FAKE_LAST_UPDATE_TIME_DATE

        static final Date FAKE_LAST_UPDATE_TIME_DATE
        This effective time has to be manually set on the TerminologymetadataPackage.getCodeSystemVersion_LastUpdateDate() feature before re-versioning an already existing version.

        This is the workaround to lie to CDO about a change, since the commit timestamp not known at commit time but on change processing time.

      • PATCHED_PREDICATE

        static final com.google.common.base.Predicate<ICodeSystemVersion> PATCHED_PREDICATE
        Predicate producing true output only and if only the processed version is patched. Otherwise false.
